body:
Hi guys. First of all, thanks for taking the time to improve the RabbitMQ implementation.

I just did a quick smoke test on this and mainly I'm wondering about how this has been tested and in which cases it works? I did a brute force shutdown of the rabbitmq server and then started it back up to see if it would reconnect. It didn't since the code doesn't have an "incremental delay reconnection strategy", that is, once a connection is lost it tries to reconnect immediately and if that fails it just gives up.

Also, unless I'm misunderstanding something, there seems to be some weirdness with the reconnection code:

```
    //connection  restart
   if (connection.isOpen()) {
      try {
          connection = connectionFactory.newConnection();
          channel.basicRecover();
```

Is that supposed to be if (connection.isOpen())? That seems weird to me.

So I would like to hear a little bit more about what testing has been done and for what scenarios this actually does re-establish a connection to the MQ.
